---
description: GitHub Etiquette
alwaysApply: true
---

# Commits
Always commit to the Dev branch. Never create a new branch.
In your commit message, give a short change log (1-2 sentences)
Only use the following command(s):
- git add
- git commit -m

# Pushes
Always push to the Dev branch. Never create a new branch
Only use the following command(s):
- git push origin dev

# Pull Requests
When making a pull request, you are to merge dev & prod.
For the PR title, title it the following: HHMM(A/)MMDDYY, which represents the date
Example: 9:00 PM on March 12, 2026 = {0900P031226}
Only use the following command(s):
- gh pr create --base prod --head dev --title {PR-TITLE}